Description: Body sherd of East Greek grey ware pottery closed vessel, probably an oinochoe; dark grey fabric core sandwiched between beige margins, with numerous mica inclusions; very worn dark slip and inscription on exterior.
Curator's comments: Gardner 1888, 47 considers that the dative plural ending in -ois cannot be in the Aeolic dialect of the area. The use of this form is indeed not found in literary Aeolic, but cannot be rules out in everyday prose.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (pl. 22.4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GL.084)
